cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the problem of mining patterns from activity-trajectory data, which is a type of sequential data. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-categories of databases (cs.DB) and information retrieval (cs.IR). Additionally, the paper addresses the issue of anonymization, which is a common concern in security and privacy (cs.CR). The proposed technique also involves pre-processing and ordering of the search space, which could fall under the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and search algorithms (cs.SI).
